writing forever.

00:15:52.530 --> 00:15:53.830
&gt;&gt; Elizabeth Strout: Right.

00:15:53.830 --> 00:15:55.360
&gt;&gt; Marie Arana: And
getting turned down,

00:15:55.360 --> 00:15:57.790
and rejections at the beginning.

00:15:57.790 --> 00:16:00.350
And then, "Olive Kitteridge"
comes along

00:16:00.350 --> 00:16:02.040 position:56%
and you get, win the Pulitzer prize.

00:16:02.040 --> 00:16:05.330 position:56%
But I have the feeling that what
you're saying, especially about "Amy

00:16:05.330 --> 00:16:08.800 position:56%
and Isabelle," is that it was a just
kind of discovery as you went along.

00:16:08.800 --> 00:16:10.100
&gt;&gt; Elizabeth Strout: Right.

00:16:10.100 --> 00:16:11.400
It was. And it always is.

00:16:11.400 --> 00:16:12.700
It always is.

00:16:12.700 --> 00:16:15.290
I never know what I'm
going to write, exactly.

00:16:15.290 --> 00:16:19.050
I have some, you know, sort
of sense, as I had that sense

00:16:19.050 --> 00:16:20.930
about the hair cutting scene.

00:16:20.930 --> 00:16:23.170
I thought, "Let's try and
earn our way to that."

00:16:23.170 --> 00:16:24.950
So I have a sense of something.

00:16:24.950 --> 00:16:28.060
And then, you know, find out all
sorts of things along the way.

00:16:28.060 --> 00:16:29.360
&gt;&gt; Marie Arana: Mm-hmm.

00:16:29.360 --> 00:16:31.290
And how did Olive come to you?

00:16:31.290 --> 00:16:34.340
How did Olive Kitteridge come to
you?What a fabulous character.

00:16:34.340 --> 00:16:35.640
&gt;&gt; Elizabeth Strout: She came to me

00:16:35.640 --> 00:16:37.010
when I was unloading
the dishwasher one day.

00:16:37.010 --> 00:16:44.720
And I just, I always, I just saw
this really large woman, you know,

00:16:44.720 --> 00:16:48.930
tall, big woman standing
near a picnic table.

00:16:48.930 --> 00:16:51.260
And I have never owned
a picnic table,

00:16:51.260 --> 00:16:53.540
and my family has never
owned a picnic table.

00:16:53.540 --> 00:16:56.790
But I saw her standing
next to a picnic table,

00:16:56.790 --> 00:17:01.690
and I could hear her thinking,
"It's high time everyone left."

00:17:01.690 --> 00:17:05.610
And I thought, I better
get that down.

00:17:05.610 --> 00:17:12.440
So I did. So I got that down, and
then once I wrote that first story,

00:17:12.440 --> 00:17:13.940
well, it wasn't the
first story in the --

00:17:13.940 --> 00:17:17.710
it was the story where she
steals her daughter-in-law's bra.

00:17:17.710 --> 00:17:21.640
Once I got that story down,
I realized, I'm going,

00:17:21.640 --> 00:17:24.790
I understood the form of
the book almost immediately,

00:17:24.790 --> 00:17:29.250
