form of the book is everything.

00:17:29.250 --> 00:17:33.420 position:56%
And so I understood that I was going
to do this in a series of stories

00:17:33.420 --> 00:17:37.500 position:56%
that had Olive, but then I
realized she's an awful lot to take.

00:17:37.500 --> 00:17:39.160
You know, we don't
want her in every page.

00:17:39.160 --> 00:17:42.440
A little too much for
me and for the reader.

00:17:42.440 --> 00:17:46.010
And so, then I began to realize
she's a part of the community.

00:17:46.010 --> 00:17:47.620
Let's look at her from
different angles.

00:17:47.620 --> 00:17:50.030
Because what interests me
so much is how, you know,

00:17:50.030 --> 00:17:51.600
when we think we know someone.

00:17:51.600 --> 00:17:52.900
And we don't.

00:17:52.900 --> 00:17:54.200
We just know this part of them.

00:17:54.200 --> 00:17:57.480
And if you live in a town and you
see another part of that person --

00:17:57.480 --> 00:17:59.510
you know, that was
very interesting to me.

00:17:59.510 --> 00:18:02.870
And so I began to, you know,
make the town around her.

00:18:02.870 --> 00:18:04.170
&gt;&gt; Marie Arana: Mm-hmm.

00:18:04.170 --> 00:18:05.470
You made her a teacher.

00:18:05.470 --> 00:18:06.770
&gt;&gt; Elizabeth Strout: Yeah.

00:18:06.770 --> 00:18:08.070
&gt;&gt; Marie Arana: Like your parents.

00:18:08.070 --> 00:18:09.370
&gt;&gt; Elizabeth Strout: Yeah.

00:18:09.370 --> 00:18:11.850
&gt;&gt; Marie Arana: Is there
anything we can draw from that?

00:18:11.850 --> 00:18:13.640
Or you're just familiar
with teaching?

00:18:13.640 --> 00:18:14.940
&gt;&gt; Elizabeth Strout:
I just think was,

00:18:14.940 --> 00:18:16.680
I just was familiar with teaching.

00:18:16.680 --> 00:18:19.130
She's a math teacher --
nobody in my family was,

00:18:19.130 --> 00:18:20.920
you know, very good in math.

00:18:20.920 --> 00:18:26.880
But I, you know, a seventh grade
math teacher just seemed to be

00:18:26.880 --> 00:18:31.230
who she was as I envisioned
her bulk.

00:18:31.230 --> 00:18:32.530
&gt;&gt; Marie Arana: Mm-hmm.

00:18:32.530 --> 00:18:34.060
Mm-hmm. Now, speaking of her bulk.

00:18:34.060 --> 00:18:37.590
There was a movie made
of "Olive Kitteridge."

00:18:37.590 --> 00:18:42.850
I haven't seen it, I prefer
to stay with the book.

00:18:42.850 --> 00:18:45.650
How did, first of all, how
did you feel about the movie?

00:18:45.650 --> 00:18:47.370
&gt;&gt; Elizabeth Strout: I thought
