00:19:05.820 --> 00:19:10.610
But I thought Frances did a
wonderful job creating her Olive.

00:19:10.610 --> 00:19:11.910
&gt;&gt; Marie Arana: So, you approve.

00:19:11.910 --> 00:19:13.210
&gt;&gt; Elizabeth Strout: I did.

00:19:13.210 --> 00:19:14.510
I really did.

00:19:14.510 --> 00:19:15.810
Yeah. Very much.

00:19:15.810 --> 00:19:17.110
&gt;&gt; Marie Arana: Did you
have anything to do with it?

00:19:17.110 --> 00:19:18.410
&gt;&gt; Elizabeth Strout: No.

00:19:18.410 --> 00:19:19.710
&gt;&gt; Marie Arana: No, no.

00:19:19.710 --> 00:19:21.010
Okay.

00:19:21.010 --> 00:19:22.310
&gt;&gt; Elizabeth Strout: I mean, I had,
you know, I had many conversations

00:19:22.310 --> 00:19:23.610
with Frances about Olive.

00:19:23.610 --> 00:19:25.790
And then I spoke to the
screen director for, I mean,

00:19:25.790 --> 00:19:28.030
the screen writer for, you know,
an hour and a half one day.

00:19:28.030 --> 00:19:31.320
And then I spoke to the
director for an hour

00:19:31.320 --> 00:19:35.490 position:56%
and a half one day, and that was it.

00:19:35.490 --> 00:19:38.300
&gt;&gt; Marie Arana: So, you
win the Pulitzer Prize.

00:19:38.300 --> 00:19:41.960
You've had this tremendous
trajectory from,

00:19:41.960 --> 00:19:45.190
